1931;;It Pays to Advertise;;American;;Frank Tuttle;;Norman Foster, Carole Lombard;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/It_Pays_to_Advertise_(film);;Rodney Martin sets up a soap business to rival his father. With the help of an advertising expert and his secretary, Mary, he develops a successful marketing campaign. His father ends up buying the company from him, while Rodney and Mary fall in love.[2]